TPS Central Support Agent
The automated help desk for TPS Central. Answers "how do I use this system" questions instantly, with role-aware routing and escalation when confidence is low. Design principle: enablement agent. Different job than Janet (intelligence) and the TPS Central Agent (input). Same platform, different knowledge base, different answer pattern.
The knowledge base is already built — the most deployment-ready component in the strategy:
Asset	Coverage
4 Job Aid JSON files (GSV, Manager, Account Management, Reporting)	93 intents, ~400 trigger phrases
Master Routing Index	Role-context routing, shared topic disambiguation, fallback logic
Bot Response Schema	Standardized output: source, matched intent, canonical answer, escalation path
TPS Central Knowledge Base	Workfront objects, touchpoint types, TD fields, sales cycle, operating model
Deployed to #tpscentral-support in Slack. Estimated 1-2 weeks from knowledge base loaded to pilot. Fastest win in the roadmap.
Example routing:
Question	Routed To	Answer
How do I reassign a Tech Driver?	Manager Job Aid	Steps to change Project Owner with field instructions
What's the difference between Tech Case and Tech Fit?	Manager Job Aid (TD Fields)	Definitions, when to update, stage-gate relationship
How do I submit a VPW request?	Account Management	Step-by-step with assignment guidance
My SV request is stuck — what do I do?	GSV Job Aid	Status definitions, escalation path, dashboard check
